    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi,\n\nin a help buf/ft, the relativenumber in a custom statuscolumn doesn't update correctly. The numbers are messed up. In other buf/filetypes this doesn't happen.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0112a429-fad1-42a5-97d7-7643b3eb0830\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n: set relativenumber\n: lua vim.opt.statuscolumn = [[%s%=%{v:relnum?v:relnum:v:lnum}│ ]]\n: e ~/.config/nvim/init.lua\n> Scroll arround - statuscolumn/line numbers are updated correctly\n\n: help map\n\n> Scroll arround - statuscolumn/line numbers are not updated correctly\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nhelp buf behaves like normal buffers\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-700+g400f247397\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, statuscolumn is nvim only\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\ngh",
